<subSubSection id="C30465748212136225A58161FE18FA97" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA136FF8212136225A58161FE52FB5E" blockId="49.[151,1436,1122,1327]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8212136225A58161FEA3FBE7" bold="true" box="[151,273,1122,1147]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Intermarginal denticles of chelicerae present (
<figureCitation id="13252A7A82121362261C8161FC24FBE6" box="[814,918,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[175,1436,199,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-59@50.[151,1436,193,1831]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 29. Eusparassus jaegeri spec. nov., holotype male from South Africa: NE of Pretoria (SMF). (a) left palp, ventral; (b) left palp, retrolateral; (c) embolus tip and conductor, ventral; (d) eye arrangement, dorsal; (e) left chelicera, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422671" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422671/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Figs 29e</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13252A7A8212136226978161FC62FBE6" box="[933,976,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="53.[151,250,1869,1892]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,202,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-52@53.[151,1436,193,1848]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="FIGURE 31. Eusparassus schoemanae spec. nov., holotype male from South Africa: Namaqualand (ZMB). (a) left palp, ventral; (b) left palp, retrolateral; (c) embolus tip and conductor, ventral; (d) eye arrangement, dorsal; (e) left chelicera, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422677/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">31e</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13252A7A8212136226ED8161FBBEFBE6" box="[991,1036,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="58.[151,250,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1408,283,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-79@58.[151,1436,265,1907]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURE 35. Eusparassus jocquei spec. nov., holotype male from Zimbabwe: Bulawayo (MRAC) (a) left palp, ventral; (b) left palp, retrolateral; (c) embolus tip and conductor, ventral; (d) eye arrangement, dorsal; (e) right chelicera, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422685/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">35e</figureCitation>
); in female epigyne, AMLL fused together and encircling MS entirely (
<figureCitation id="13252A7A8212136227718185FD1BFB02" box="[579,681,1158,1182]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1869,1892]" captionTargetBox="[160,1435,201,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-87@51.[151,1436,193,1848]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 30. Eusparassus jaegeri spec. nov.: (a–c) paratype female from South Africa: NE of Pretoria (SMF); (d) female from South Africa Klein Kariba (PPRI). (a) epigyne, ventral; (b) vulva, dorsal; (c–d) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422673/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Figs 30a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13252A7A82121362278A8185FD51FB02" box="[696,739,1158,1182]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1683,1706]" captionTargetBox="[153,1419,219,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-146@54.[151,1436,218,1646]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 32. Eusparassus schoemanae spec. nov., paratype female from South Africa: E of Kamieskroon (NMSA). (a) epigyne, ventral; (b) vulva, dorsal; (c) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422679/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">32a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13252A7A8212136227C08185FCAEFB02" box="[754,796,1158,1182]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="56.[151,250,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[158,1424,195,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-62@56.[151,1436,195,1859]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 34. Eusparassus borakalalo spec. nov., (a–e) holotype and (f) paratype female from South Africa: Borakalalo Natural Reserve. (a, f) epigyne, ventral; (b) vulva, dorsal; (c) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral; (d) right chelicera, ventral; (e) eye arrangement, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422683/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">34a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13252A7A8212136226198185FCE5FB02" box="[811,855,1158,1182]" captionStart="FIGURE 36" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1730,1753]" captionTargetBox="[161,1433,193,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-131@59.[151,1436,193,1709]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 36. Eusparassus jocquei spec. nov., paratype female from Zimbabwe: Bulawayo (MRAC). (a) epigyne, ventral; (b) vulva, dorsal; (c) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422687" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422687/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">36a</figureCitation>
); male palp exhibiting an obviously enlarged subtegulum (
<figureCitation id="13252A7A82121362243381A9FED7FB5E" box="[257,357,1194,1218]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[175,1436,199,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-59@50.[151,1436,193,1831]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 29. Eusparassus jaegeri spec. nov., holotype male from South Africa: NE of Pretoria (SMF). (a) left palp, ventral; (b) left palp, retrolateral; (c) embolus tip and conductor, ventral; (d) eye arrangement, dorsal; (e) left chelicera, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422671" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422671/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Figs 29a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13252A7A82121362244381A9FE29FB5E" box="[369,411,1194,1218]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="53.[151,250,1869,1892]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,202,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-52@53.[151,1436,193,1848]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="FIGURE 31. Eusparassus schoemanae spec. nov., holotype male from South Africa: Namaqualand (ZMB). (a) left palp, ventral; (b) left palp, retrolateral; (c) embolus tip and conductor, ventral; (d) eye arrangement, dorsal; (e) left chelicera, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422677/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">31a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13252A7A82121362249581A9FE61FB5E" box="[423,467,1194,1218]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="58.[151,250,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1408,283,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-79@58.[151,1436,265,1907]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURE 35. Eusparassus jocquei spec. nov., holotype male from Zimbabwe: Bulawayo (MRAC) (a) left palp, ventral; (b) left palp, retrolateral; (c) embolus tip and conductor, ventral; (d) eye arrangement, dorsal; (e) right chelicera, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422685/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">35a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136FF8212136225F581CDFE18FA97" blockId="49.[151,1436,1122,1327]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
